    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy  <br>
intro- <br>
This deck is quite interesting. As you can see the shadow is a really strong Nazgul/wound deck, while the free peoples side combines Elven archery Elven fighting power to create a very strong deck. You have many different ways to win with this deck. It is mainly a multi-player deck and is desinged to be able to compete vs all different minion types.  you usually start Arwen and legolas.  If you go first your opponent probably has nazgul so start prince of mirkwood.  if you go second they are probably using moria or something else so start greenleaf.  Wither way always start arwen.<br>
<br>
top cards- <br>
Well while every card in this deck is important, some are more important than others. for free peoples the top cards are: <br>
A Ranger&#39;s Versatility. It lets you exhaust 2 minios at a river or forest. This is a very good card. once the minios are exhausted, you ca use cards like Power According to His Stature to finish off minions. <br>
Power According To His Stature. It lets Frodo (or sam if he has the ring) to wound every minion against him. Why it works in this deck is that because of archery and ranger&#39;s versatility you can make ay minion, even a cave troll or witch king fall at the power of this card. <br>
Gwemegil. It makes Arwen very strong, as well as allowing you to cycle cards through your hand. <br>
<br>
All Blades Perish. A great card for Nazgul if you are facing an archery deck. <br>
Blade Tip/Black Breath. This combo basically wounds the companion it ids on every turn, and prevents you from healing him! wow. <br>
<br>
how it beats you. <br>
To start don&#39;t bid anything. You want to go second so you are playig on your sites, but if you have to go first use ulaire Nelya to covert sites. For the shadow deck play as many guys ad conditions as you can each turn. the bigger the pool the better cause you can get more guys out. Most ofthe Nazgul have specail abilities, so use them. Cantea and Attea Are particularly nasty with being able to discard weapons and increase strength. <br>
The free peoples deck is strong. Don&#39;t play too many guys in one turn. try to have out 4 or 5 guys but not all nine at once. try to do as much archery as you can each turn. Many times you will kill all the minions before a single skirmish happens. A ranger&#39;s versatility really helps with archery. If anything makes it through archery then they have to deal with arwen ad legolas. They both get a strength bonus vs Nazgul, don&#39;t forget it. Gwemegil, Bow of Galadhrim, Asfaloth, Defiance and Border Defenses will help you win the skirmishes. Use the rare aragorn when you are getting swarmed. The seen and unseen helps vs sauron conditions which are very nasty. speaking of conditions you may notice there isn&#39;t a lot of free people codition removal. that&#39;s because it isn&#39;t needed. vs nazgul you will win skirmishes so blade tip doesn&#39;t hurt. vs sauron you have stand against darkness. vs moria you have archery. vs uruk-hai it&#39;s tough if they cancel the archery phase or if they cancel skirmish events, but if they do just sacrifice some lorien elves. <br>
<br>
top card- <br>
A Ranger&#39;s Versatility. It exhausts 2 minions. after that you ow them, using archery, legolas&#39;s bow, power according to his stature and other cards. it is a game-breaker. <br>
<br>
thanks for reading <br>
brad eier <br>
bacon 2 <br>
